originalText.text: DO NOT PARK HERE!!!  I showed up 30 minutes after the 24 hour rate expired ($30). They refused to pro-rate the 30 minutes (~$5 at most nyc garages) and wanted more than double the 24 hour rate ($76). They also refused access to my vehicle if I wanted to leave it.  You can only complain to an automated line that will not answer.  Park across the street. 24 hour access to your vehicle for only $6 more (24hr rate).  Way more friendly too.

originalText.text: This parking garage lied about their address in order to avoid giving a lower advertised price to park. They charge $38 instead of $21 and claimed they were unable to refund a credit card charge. Luckily I am protected because I use American Express. To add to the lack of professionalism at this garage, the attended proceeded to call me "mami".

AVOID Quik Park, as they have no integrity...
